The paper deals with privacy protection of trajectory data, which is a common concern in the field of computer security (cs.CR). The proposed method involves data sanitization, which is a common technique used in database management (cs.DB). The method also involves classification and correlation analysis, which are common techniques used in machine learning and data mining (cs.LG, cs.SI). Finally, the paper proposes a randomized response mechanism, which is a common technique used in information retrieval (cs.IR).
